 ## Deployed Services
 
-The local deployment creates the following Docker services:
+The local deployment creates the following Docker services, all accessible through a single entry point:
+
+- **onearth-demo** - Main entry point (configurable port, default: 80)
+  - Proxies all requests to appropriate backend services
+  - Serves interactive demo page with endpoint testing
+  - Routes WMTS, TWMS, and WMS requests to backend services
+
+Backend services (internal Docker network only, not directly accessible from host):
+- **onearth-tile-services** - WMTS/TWMS tile serving
+- **onearth-capabilities** - GetCapabilities and metadata services
+- **onearth-time-service** - Time dimension support (Redis)
+- **onearth-reproject** - On-the-fly reprojection service
+- **onearth-wms** - WMS service
 
-- **onearth-demo** (port 80) - Interactive demo page with endpoint testing
-- **onearth-capabilities** (port 8081) - WMTS GetCapabilities and metadata services
-- **onearth-tile-services** (port 443) - WMTS tile serving
-- **onearth-time-service** (port 6379) - Time dimension support
-- **onearth-reproject** (port 8082) - On-the-fly reprojection service
-- **onearth-wms** (port 8443) - WMS service
+### Multiple Instance Deployment
+
+You can run multiple OnEarth instances on the same host by using different ports:
+
+```bash
+# Production instance on port 80
+./setup-onearth-local.sh --port 80
+
+# Development instance on port 8080 (in different terminal/directory)
+cd /path/to/dev/onearth
+./docker/local-deployment/setup-onearth-local.sh --port 8080
+
+# Laptop/testing instance on port 3000
+./setup-onearth-local.sh --port 3000
+```
+
+Each instance operates independently with its own containers and can use different data directories.
 
